                    <span>I'll keep it short. I only wish that when I was in school history had been taught using tools like this book. It paints such a realistic view of life when our country was young.  I felt as if I were there and knew (and liked) these people. They came more and more alive with every page.  What an extraordinary woman with, despite the hardships, a relationship with her husband to be envied.  I'm so glad it has been re-released.  My present copy is second hand - there were no new copies to be had a few years ago.  I recommend it without reservation!</span>
                  
              
